%I A316198 #14 Jun 21 2026 18:59:29
%S A316198 0,2,6,59,695,12198,240549,5191160,118346760,2816763296
%N A316198 Number of self-avoiding polygons with perimeter 2*n and sides = 1 that have vertex angles from the set 0, +-Pi/4, +-Pi/2, +-3*Pi/4, not counting rotations and reflections as distinct.
%C A316198 Holes are excluded, i.e., the boundary path may nowhere touch or intersect itself.
%C A316198 From _Anton Pirogov_, Jun 21 2026: (Start)
%C A316198 Also number of free simple matchstick polygons with perimeter 2*n on the cyclotomic ring Z[zeta_8].
%C A316198 The values a(7)-a(10) were determined by enumeration with the tilezz library using exact cyclotomic integer arithmetic over Z[zeta_8]. (End)
%H A316198 Contest Organizers, <a href="http://www.recmath.org/contest/Snakes/index.php">Al Zimmermann's Programming Contests - Snakes on a Plane</a>, Fall 2006.
%H A316198 Hugo Pfoertner, <a href="http://www.randomwalk.de/sequences/a316198.htm">Illustration of polygons of perimeter <= 10</a>.
%H A316198 Anton Pirogov, <a href="https://github.com/apirogov/tilezz">tilezz</a> - exact cyclotomic geometry library including a polygon enumerator.
%H A316198 Anton Pirogov, <a href="https://ratdb.app.pirogov.de">Rat Explorer</a> - interactive database of cyclotomic matchstick polygons.
%H A316198 Anton Pirogov, <a href="https://github.com/apirogov/tilezz-ratdb">RatDB datasets</a> - reproducible datasets containing the enumerated polygons.
%Y A316198 Cf. A306178, A316195, A316197.
%K A316198 nonn,walk,more
%O A316198 1,2
%A A316198 _Hugo Pfoertner_, Jul 04 2018
%E A316198 a(7)-a(10) from _Anton Pirogov_, Jun 21 2026
